node.text:
Hi everyone!

I'm so excited to announce that Thiago is @campaignoaat's next campaign kid! They are on a mission to raise $10,000 this month to fund a trip for our family to Disney World in Orlando, FL along with some extra fun and support along the way! They are also selling #ThiagoStrong bracelets on their website in exchange for a $20 donation to Thiago’s campaign! You can make a contribution and get your bracelet via the link in our bio! We are so grateful to be chosen for this campaign! We need all your support to get the word out. Even without a contribution, sharing the post would be a huge help as well!

Thank you,
The Cortez Family

#thiagostrong #cancersurvivor #chemosurvivor #chemowarrior #cancerwarrior #pediatriccancer #kidneycancer

node.text:
It’s Friday! and to be honest this week has been a blur to me. So many unexpected emotions have completely drained me, but I haven’t let that stop me from completing my daily exercise routine. It’s doing so much for my mental health as well as giving me the energy to tackle the day! 

Also, with the news we received on Tuesday from the doctors, we will continue to homeschool Thiago until we feel it’s safe for him to join a school. This was the year we planned for him to start school. On a positive note, I get to start getting his learning area ready. Plus I’m not ready for him to leave me yet! 

Do you have the new year plan set out? Will you be doing remote learning, in school, or homeschool learning?

node.text:
Happy 2️⃣2️⃣ Birthday Elinne! 🎂

To the girl who changed my life! I’m so proud of you, and cannot wait to see you continue to hit life goals as you enter these fun years of adulthood! You are the best protective sister to your not so little sister, and you have the most patience for your little brother. May God continue to protect you and guide you.
I love you so very much, enjoy your day my sweet girl!💗

node.text:
After seven grueling months, of Thiago fighting Cancer, we are elated to announce that he is CANCER FREE!! 

I just wanted to share this incredible news with you all! Thank you for the support and prayers we received from this community! 🙏🏻🎗

node.text:
This past week has been a tough one. To be honest, I didn’t feel like posting. I just wanted to relax and start processing. Since we were on the go, these past seven months. I’m finally able to slow down and let everything sink in. These emotions are indescribable. I will take my time to adjust to our new norm. Meanwhile, I will post bits and pieces of our lives on here. 

Today we have our end of treatment scans! To start off, Thiago has to get accessed for the contrast meds. So we will be going to clinic for that before heading over to radiology. Tomorrow we will have our appointment with our oncology team to get results! Please continue to pray for our family. 🙏🏻

node.text:
I started working on our pretend play area this weekend. I wanted to create a camping set up for Thiago since he has been asking to go lately. As I started taking out toys, he found the fishing rod and climbed on the rocker and said, “look mommy I’m fishing!” Pretend play is definitely magical at this age! 🎣

We hope to make plans for a camping trip in the near future. However, we can’t go quite yet, due to just finishing chemo. Maybe in a few months. Have you been camping this year? If so where have you visited? 🏕

node.text:
It is now week THREE of our campaign with @campaignoaat ! After such an exciting day of ringing the bell, we had to take the following days pretty easy. Thiago woke up nauseous and wasn’t feeling like himself. His appetite is not there, so I’m hoping the side effects wear off soon. 

We thought we’d share a short Q&A with you! Thank you so much to everyone who has helped us throughout this campaign to help Thiago get to Disney World! We have ten days left of his campaign! Link in bio to order your very own #thiagostrong bracelet ☺️

node.text:
Watch me ring the bell! 🔔

This day couldn’t come any faster! It hit me like a ton a bricks when I came home and saw the video of him ringing the bell!! A flood of emotions was definitely let out! 😭

 I feel so overwhelmed at the moment, I will have to call it a night for today. But not before saying thank you again for supporting us through this journey.🎗

node.text:
I wanted to share this book that was sent to us by a dear friend. Thiago was having a hard time with the second haircut he received a couple of weeks ago. So I decided to help him visualize with this portrait of himself sister drew. We hole- punched the top of the head to place string for him to have a practice at scissors! ✂️

With our last chemo appointment being today, I’ve been a mess. Especially with the unknown after treatment. It feels like the safety net we’ve had is going to disappear. People may say, “yay you guys are done, now back to normalcy!” But in reality we are never done, our lives will never go back to normal. Our normal has forever changed. This will be yet another transition we will have to work on. 🎗

I just wanted to Thank you all for your support during our journey. This IG community has been amazing to our family! 💛

node.text:
Pronouncing dinosaurs names with Thiago! 

If you have been following us for a while, you know the love of dinosaurs is very much a thing in our household. I’ve learned so many informative facts about dinosaurs with all the fun activities I’ve set up for him. 

So I decided to record him pronouncing the dinosaur names. These will be memories I will be able to come back too! Also, did you know how to pronounce most of these dinosaur names? 

Flashcards: @nestling_and_nook

🦈 FEED THE SHARK GAME 🦈

I wanted to create a visual for Thiago to see a comparison to how big the megalodon’s mouth was to the animals it ate! 

I used an empty cardboard box to make the visual. I cut out the mouth and Alessandra painted the shark! I think she did a fantastic job with it! Then I found animals Thiago could feed to the Megalodon! 

To make it more of a challenge, I decided to add our balance beam. Thiago walked the beam, when he got to the end he grabbed a fish, then would try to make into the mouth. This was an amazing indoors activity perfect for these hot summer days. 

If you like this activity, you can save this for later! And if you have friends that would enjoy our activities, please tag them in the comments below!⬇️

node.text:
This week has kept us very busy, but I wanted to do some fun shark themed activities in honor of shark week. 
Since Thiago loves dinosaurs, why not learn about the Megalodon! 🦈 

Did you know the Megalodon was the largest fish that ever lived with the length of 15 to 18 meters? It’s diet consisted of whales, sharks, seals, sea lions, walruses, and fish.

This was our first lesson I set up for him in a long time. It made me so happy seeing how much he enjoyed it! I also created a fun activity for him to visualize a smaller size of the megalodon’s mouth. Can’t wait to share it with you! 😉

node.accessibility_caption: Smiling pediatric cancer patient in his playroom

node.text:
Although you might see a happy child smiling in front of the camera, you don’t see those moments of pain. Countless tears are shed daily. Chemo is the drug that’s saving him but is also wreaking so much havoc on his tiny body. This is cancer; tears, pain, nausea, lack of appetite, mouth sores, weak immune system. 

As a warrior mom, I sometimes feel alone, abandoned by friends and family who don’t understand what it’s like to walk this path. But my faith in God has not hindered and I’m reminded I am not alone. 

It’s hard for me to put my emotions out there, but I’m feeling quite emotional with our last chemo treatment less than a week away. I’m so thankful for social media where I can let it out in hopes of reaching that parent that’s felt, or feeling alone, because there is always a community of warriors ready to listen. 🧡🎗
